str2: However, nevertheless, but, except that, yet. From pleion; moreover, i.e. Albeit, save that, rather, yet.

str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.

str2: Third person singular active present of deo; also deon deh-on'; neuter active participle of the same; both used impersonally; it is Necessary.

str2: Today, now. Neuter of a presumed compound of the article ho and hemera; on the day; generally, now.
Tomorrow. From a derivative of the same as aer; properly, fresh, i.e. to-morrow.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

str2: To have, hold, possess. Including an alternate form scheo skheh'-o; a primary verb; to hold.
Neuter of hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that; causative, because.

str2: To allow, it is possible. Third person singular present of a compound of en and dechomai; it is accepted in, i.e. Admitted.
From a compound of pro and phemi; a foreteller; by analogy, an inspired speaker; by extension, a poet.
From apo and the base of olethros; to destroy fully, literally or figuratively.
Without, outside. Adverb from ek; out(-side, of doors), literally or figuratively.
Of Hebrew origin; Hierusalem, the capitol of Palestine.
